{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Limit Lord Mayor Tenure to Two Terms",
        "additional_details": "Currently no statutory maximum prevents repeat appointments.\r\n\r\nWe believe a two-term cap will:\r\n\r\nBroaden representation across political parties, wards and demographics.\r\nEncourage fresh leadership and new ideas.\r\nSafeguard institutional integrity by preventing undue influence\r\n\r\nWe call on the Government to draft and enact the necessary legislation at the earliest opportunity and to issue guidance for local authorities so this term limit can take effect at the start of the next municipal year.\r\n",
        "background": "Limit the number of terms an individual may serve as Lord Mayor or Mayor to two terms in any local authority by amending existing local government legislation and requiring councils to update their standing orders accordingly.",
